urls.description: Provides access to the 'LDlink' API (<https://ldlink.nci.nih.gov/?tab=apiaccess>) using the R console. This programmatic access facilitates researchers who are interested in performing batch queries in 1000 Genomes Project (2015) <doi:10.1038/nature15393> data using 'LDlink'. 'LDlink' is an interactive and powerful suite of web-based tools for querying germline variants in human population groups of interest. For more details, please see Machiela et al. (2015) <doi:10.1093/bioinformatics/btv402>.

model <- glm(response ~ explanatory_variable, family = poisson(link = "log"), data = dataset)

3/10: üìêThe main components of a GLM are:

Random Component: The response variable's distribution (e.g., Gaussian, Poisson, Binomial)
Systematic Component: Linear predictor (linear combo of explanatory variables)
Link Function: Connects the two components. #Rstats #DataScience
